The White House Office of the Press Secretary held a press briefing with Press Secretary Jay Carney on July 16, 2013. Carney addressed several topics including the emerging deal in the Senate to move forward on the confirmation of President Obama's nominees, Edward Snowden's application for temporary asylum in Russia, sexual assault in the military, the Trayvon Martin case, immigration reform, and the situation in Egypt. Carney emphasized the President's support for the confirmation of his nominees and the need for reconciliation and a return to democratically elected civilian government in Egypt. He also mentioned the President's belief in the importance of conversations about race and his focus on improving the lives of everyday Americans through concrete actions.